Road accidents drive families into poverty as victims are often breadwinners, noted Richard Scurfield of the World Bank.
China faces a grim prediction of half a million annual deaths by 2020 due to road traffic fatalities.
Factors like speeding and drunken driving contribute to the high death rate.
Safety measures, such as seat belt enforcement, are being implemented worldwide.
In Uganda, strict traffic regulations are being enforced, with fines for passengers not wearing seat belts.
ASEAN countries are also working to enhance road safety standards and promote awareness among citizens.
The goal is to prevent unnecessary injuries and fatalities on the roads.
